jnxAtm.name: jnxAtm

revisions.description: The following new objects were added: - jnxAtmVCOutOAMF5AISCells (jnxAtmVCTable). - jnxAtmTrunkOutOAMF4AISCells (jnxAtmTrunkTable).
Renamed atmTcc as atmTccVcMux. atmTccSnap encapsulation added.

jnxAtm.contactinfo: Juniper Technical Assistance Center Juniper Networks, Inc. 1194 N. Mathilda Avenue Sunnyvale, CA 94089 E-mail: support@juniper.net
jnxAtm.description: The Juniper enterprise MIB for ATM interfaces and VCs

JnxAtmFlags.name: JnxAtmFlags
JnxAtmFlags.description: Flags related to the VC or Trunk.

jnxAtmIfTable.name: jnxAtmIfTable
jnxAtmIfTable.description: This table contains config and stats parameters, one entry per physical interface (ATM port).

jnxAtmIfEntry.name: jnxAtmIfEntry
jnxAtmIfEntry.description: This entry contains additional ATM interface config and stats objects, not covered in standard mibs. Each entry is an extension of atmInterfaceConfEntry defined in ATM-MIB.

jnxAtmIfScrambleEnable.name: jnxAtmIfScrambleEnable
jnxAtmIfScrambleEnable.description: Shows whether scrambling is enabled or disabled

jnxAtmIfTxCellCount.name: jnxAtmIfTxCellCount
jnxAtmIfTxCellCount.description: The number of ATM cells transmitted by the interface. Includes Idle cells transmitted.

jnxAtmIfRxCellCount.name: jnxAtmIfRxCellCount
jnxAtmIfRxCellCount.description: The number of ATM cells received by the interface. Excludes Idle cells received.

jnxAtmIfTxIdleCellCount.name: jnxAtmIfTxIdleCellCount
jnxAtmIfTxIdleCellCount.description: The number of idle cells sent by the port. When the ATM interface has nothing to send, it sends idle cells to fill the time slot.

jnxAtmIfUncorrHCSErrs.name: jnxAtmIfUncorrHCSErrs
jnxAtmIfUncorrHCSErrs.description: The number of uncorrectable cell Header Check Sequence (HCS) Errors that occurred.

jnxAtmIfCorrHCSErrs.name: jnxAtmIfCorrHCSErrs
jnxAtmIfCorrHCSErrs.description: The number of correctable cell Header Check Sequence (HCS) Errors that occurred.

jnxAtmIfTxCellFIFOOverRuns.name: jnxAtmIfTxCellFIFOOverRuns
jnxAtmIfTxCellFIFOOverRuns.description: The number of overruns in the Transmit FIFO.

jnxAtmIfRxCellFIFOOverRuns.name: jnxAtmIfRxCellFIFOOverRuns
jnxAtmIfRxCellFIFOOverRuns.description: The number of overruns in the Receive FIFO.

jnxAtmIfRxCellFIFOUnderRuns.name: jnxAtmIfRxCellFIFOUnderRuns
jnxAtmIfRxCellFIFOUnderRuns.description: The number of underruns in the receive FIFO.

jnxAtmIfInInvalidVCCells.name: jnxAtmIfInInvalidVCCells
jnxAtmIfInInvalidVCCells.description: The number of Cells that arrived for non existent VC.

jnxAtmIfInNoBufferOAMCells.name: jnxAtmIfInNoBufferOAMCells
jnxAtmIfInNoBufferOAMCells.description: The number of received OAM cells or raw cells dropped because no buffers were available to handle them.

jnxAtmIfInNoBufDropPkts.name: jnxAtmIfInNoBufDropPkts
jnxAtmIfInNoBufDropPkts.description: The number of AAL5 packets dropped because there was no enough buffer to handle them.

jnxAtmIfOutVCQueueDrops.name: jnxAtmIfOutVCQueueDrops
jnxAtmIfOutVCQueueDrops.description: The number of packets dropped because of queue limits on each VC.

jnxAtmIfInBadCrcs.name: jnxAtmIfInBadCrcs
jnxAtmIfInBadCrcs.description: The total number of incoming CRC errors.

jnxAtmIfInLenErrPkts.name: jnxAtmIfInLenErrPkts
jnxAtmIfInLenErrPkts.description: The number of AAL5 packets dropped because their length was incorrect.

jnxAtmIfInTimeoutPkts.name: jnxAtmIfInTimeoutPkts
jnxAtmIfInTimeoutPkts.description: The number of AAL5 packets dropped because of reassembly timeout.

jnxAtmIfL2CircuitMode.name: jnxAtmIfL2CircuitMode
jnxAtmIfL2CircuitMode.description: The layer 2 circuit mode of this Atm interface. Note, this applies only to interfaces on AtmII pics.

jnxAtmVCTable.name: jnxAtmVCTable
jnxAtmVCTable.description: A table of all p2p/p2mp/multicast VC entries.

jnxAtmVCEntry.name: jnxAtmVCEntry
jnxAtmVCEntry.description: Special Cases: - No traffic Stats for multicast VCs. (0 by default). - Multipoint Destination IP Address for a p2p vc is invalid (0.0.0.0 by default). - When the encapsulation type for the logical interface (to which VC belongs) is 'atmCccCellRelay', only Generic VC Info is valid. - If OAM is disabled (indicated in jnxAtmVCFlags), then all the OAM config & F5 stats info is invalid. (zeroed by default).

jnxAtmVCConnType.name: jnxAtmVCConnType
jnxAtmVCConnType.description: The type of connection. The type 'other' means vc type is unknown or is not one of the other types.

jnxAtmVCEncapsulation.name: jnxAtmVCEncapsulation
jnxAtmVCEncapsulation.description: The atm encapsulation type associated with the VC. atmCccCellRelay : ATM Cell Relay for CCC atmCccVcMux : ATM VC for CCC atmCiscoNlpid : Cisco-compatible ATM NLPID encapsulation atmNlpid : ATM NLPID encapsulation atmSnap : ATM LLC/SNAP encapsulation atmVcMux : ATM VC multiplexing atmTccVcMux : TCC (Translational Cross Connection) over ATM VC MUX encapsulation atmTccSnap : TCC (Translational Cross Connection) over ATM LLC/SNAP encapsulation

jnxAtmVCMpDestIPv4Addr.name: jnxAtmVCMpDestIPv4Addr
jnxAtmVCMpDestIPv4Addr.description: This object is meaningful only if jnxAtmVCConnType value is 'p2mp' (point-to-multipoint). For a p2mp VC, it's the multipoint destination IPv4 address. When the VC connection type is other than p2mp OR when the multipoint destination address type is of IPv6, this object returns 0.0.0.0 by default.

jnxAtmVCMpDestIPv6Addr.name: jnxAtmVCMpDestIPv6Addr
jnxAtmVCMpDestIPv6Addr.description: This object is meaningful only if jnxAtmVCConnType value is 'p2mp' (point-to-multipoint). For a p2mp VC, it's the multipoint destination IPv6 address. When the VC connection type is other than p2mp OR when the multipoint destination address type is of IPv4, this object returns all the bytes of addr filled with 0.

jnxAtmVCTotalDownTime.name: jnxAtmVCTotalDownTime
jnxAtmVCTotalDownTime.description: The total VC down time in seconds ever since the system rebooted.

jnxAtmVCInBytes.name: jnxAtmVCInBytes
jnxAtmVCInBytes.description: The number of bytes received on the VC.

jnxAtmVCOutBytes.name: jnxAtmVCOutBytes
jnxAtmVCOutBytes.description: The number of bytes sent out on the VC.

jnxAtmVCInPkts.name: jnxAtmVCInPkts
jnxAtmVCInPkts.description: The number of packets received on the VC.

jnxAtmVCOutPkts.name: jnxAtmVCOutPkts
jnxAtmVCOutPkts.description: The number of packets sent out on the VC.

jnxAtmVCTailQueuePktDrops.name: jnxAtmVCTailQueuePktDrops
jnxAtmVCTailQueuePktDrops.description: The number of packets dropped due to bandwidth constraints. Indicates that packets were queued to send out at a rate faster than allowed.

jnxAtmVCOAMPeriod.name: jnxAtmVCOAMPeriod
jnxAtmVCOAMPeriod.description: This time interval indicates how often the F5 cells are sent to know the status of the VC.

jnxAtmVCOAMUpCellCount.name: jnxAtmVCOAMUpCellCount
jnxAtmVCOAMUpCellCount.description: The minimum number of loopback cells to be received to declare that the VC is up.

jnxAtmVCOAMDownCellCount.name: jnxAtmVCOAMDownCellCount
jnxAtmVCOAMDownCellCount.description: The minimum number of loopback cells to be received to declare that the VC is down. This object would have zero value if OAM is not enabled. (indicated in jnxAtmVCFlags)

jnxAtmVCInOAMF5LoopCells.name: jnxAtmVCInOAMF5LoopCells
jnxAtmVCInOAMF5LoopCells.description: The number of OAM F5 loopback cells received. This object would have zero value if OAM (as indicated in jnxAtmVCFlags) is not enabled.

jnxAtmVCOutOAMF5LoopCells.name: jnxAtmVCOutOAMF5LoopCells
jnxAtmVCOutOAMF5LoopCells.description: The number of OAM F5 loopback cells sent. This object would have zero value if OAM (as indicated in jnxAtmVCFlags) is not enabled.

jnxAtmVCInOAMF5RDICells.name: jnxAtmVCInOAMF5RDICells
jnxAtmVCInOAMF5RDICells.description: The number of OAM F5 cells received, with RDI(Remote Defect Indication) bit set. This object would have zero value if OAM (as indicated in jnxAtmVCFlags) is not enabled.

jnxAtmVCOutOAMF5RDICells.name: jnxAtmVCOutOAMF5RDICells
jnxAtmVCOutOAMF5RDICells.description: The number of OAM F5 cells transmitted, with RDI(Remote Defect Indication) bit set. This object would have zero value if OAM (as indicated in jnxAtmVCFlags) is not enabled.

jnxAtmVCInOAMF5AISCells.name: jnxAtmVCInOAMF5AISCells
jnxAtmVCInOAMF5AISCells.description: The number of OAM F5 cells received, with AIS(Alarm Indication Signal) bit set. This object would have zero value if OAM (as indicated in jnxAtmVCFlags) is not enabled.

jnxAtmVCOutOAMF5AISCells.name: jnxAtmVCOutOAMF5AISCells
jnxAtmVCOutOAMF5AISCells.description: The number of OAM F5 cells transmitted, with AIS (Alarm Indication Signal) bit set. This object would have zero value if OAM (as indicated in jnxAtmVCFlags) is not enabled.

jnxAtmVpTable.name: jnxAtmVpTable
jnxAtmVpTable.description: The table of ATM VPs. This table augments atmVplTable defined in standard ATM mib.

jnxAtmVpEntry.name: jnxAtmVpEntry
jnxAtmVpEntry.description: Each entry represents config, status and statistics info related to an ATM VP configured. This entry augments the atmVplEntry defined in standard ATM mib (RFC 2515). So ifIndex and VPI are the indices to this table. Caveats: - Traffic stats are available per VP tunnel, only if shaping is configured on the VP. Object 'jnxAtmVpFlags' can be used to determine if shaping is enabled. - When no OAM is configured, OAM config and OAM stat objects' values are invalid (zero by default). Object 'jnxAtmVpFlags' contains info on whether OAM is configured or not. - For atm-1 VPs, the only valid object is jnxAtmVpFlags.

jnxAtmVpFlags.name: jnxAtmVpFlags
jnxAtmVpFlags.description: The flags associated with this VP.

jnxAtmVpTotalDownTime.name: jnxAtmVpTotalDownTime
jnxAtmVpTotalDownTime.description: The total VP downtime in seconds, ever since the system rebooted.

jnxAtmVpOamPeriod.name: jnxAtmVpOamPeriod
jnxAtmVpOamPeriod.description: This time interval indicates how often the OAM F4 cells are sent to determine the status of the VP. The value of this object is zero when OAM is not enabled on the VP. Object 'jnxAtmVpFlags' can be used to determine if OAM is enabled.

jnxAtmVpOamUpCellCount.name: jnxAtmVpOamUpCellCount
jnxAtmVpOamUpCellCount.description: The minimum number of consecutive loopback cells to be received to declare that the VP is up. The value of this object is zero when OAM is not enabled on the VP. Object 'jnxAtmVpFlags' can be used to determine if OAM is enabled.

jnxAtmVpOamDownCellCount.name: jnxAtmVpOamDownCellCount
jnxAtmVpOamDownCellCount.description: The minimum number of consecutive loopback cells to be received to declare that the VP is down. The value of this object is zero when OAM is not enabled on the VP. Object 'jnxAtmVpFlags' can be used to determine if OAM is enabled.

jnxAtmVpInBytes.name: jnxAtmVpInBytes
jnxAtmVpInBytes.description: The number of bytes received on the VP.

jnxAtmVpOutBytes.name: jnxAtmVpOutBytes
jnxAtmVpOutBytes.description: The number of bytes sent out on the VP.

jnxAtmVpInPkts.name: jnxAtmVpInPkts
jnxAtmVpInPkts.description: The number of packets received on the VP.

jnxAtmVpOutPkts.name: jnxAtmVpOutPkts
jnxAtmVpOutPkts.description: The number of packets sent out on the VP.

jnxAtmVpInOamF4Cells.name: jnxAtmVpInOamF4Cells
jnxAtmVpInOamF4Cells.description: The number of OAM F4 cells received on the VP.

jnxAtmVpOutOamF4Cells.name: jnxAtmVpOutOamF4Cells
jnxAtmVpOutOamF4Cells.description: The number of OAM F4 cells transmitted on the VP.

jnxAtmVpInOamF4LoopCells.name: jnxAtmVpInOamF4LoopCells
jnxAtmVpInOamF4LoopCells.description: The number of OAM F4 loopback cells received on the VP.

jnxAtmVpOutOamF4LoopCells.name: jnxAtmVpOutOamF4LoopCells
jnxAtmVpOutOamF4LoopCells.description: The number of OAM F4 cells transmitted on the VP.

jnxAtmVpInOamF4RdiCells.name: jnxAtmVpInOamF4RdiCells
jnxAtmVpInOamF4RdiCells.description: The number of OAM F4 RDI cells received on the VP.

jnxAtmVpOutOamF4RdiCells.name: jnxAtmVpOutOamF4RdiCells
jnxAtmVpOutOamF4RdiCells.description: The number of OAM F4 RDI cells transmitted on the VP.

jnxAtmVpInOamF4AisCells.name: jnxAtmVpInOamF4AisCells
jnxAtmVpInOamF4AisCells.description: The number of OAM F4 AIS cells received on the VP.

jnxAtmTrunkTable.name: jnxAtmTrunkTable
jnxAtmTrunkTable.description: A table of all ATM Trunk entries.

jnxAtmTrunkEntry.name: jnxAtmTrunkEntry
jnxAtmTrunkEntry.description: Special Cases: - When the encapsulation type for the logical interface (to which Trunk belongs) is 'atmCccCellRelay', only Generic Trunk Info is valid.

jnxAtmTrunkId.name: jnxAtmTrunkId
jnxAtmTrunkId.description: The identifier for this ATM Trunk.

jnxAtmTrunkConnType.name: jnxAtmTrunkConnType
jnxAtmTrunkConnType.description: The type of connection. The type 'other' means trunk type is unknown or is not one of the other types.

jnxAtmTrunkEncapsulation.name: jnxAtmTrunkEncapsulation
jnxAtmTrunkEncapsulation.description: The atm encapsulation type associated with the VC or Trunk. atmCccCellRelay : ATM Cell Relay for CCC

jnxAtmTrunkTotalDownTime.name: jnxAtmTrunkTotalDownTime
jnxAtmTrunkTotalDownTime.description: The total Trunk down time in seconds ever since the system rebooted.

jnxAtmTrunkInBytes.name: jnxAtmTrunkInBytes
jnxAtmTrunkInBytes.description: The number of bytes received on the Trunk.

jnxAtmTrunkOutBytes.name: jnxAtmTrunkOutBytes
jnxAtmTrunkOutBytes.description: The number of bytes sent out on the Trunk.

jnxAtmTrunkInPkts.name: jnxAtmTrunkInPkts
jnxAtmTrunkInPkts.description: The number of packets received on the Trunk.

jnxAtmTrunkOutPkts.name: jnxAtmTrunkOutPkts
jnxAtmTrunkOutPkts.description: The number of packets sent out on the Trunk.

jnxAtmTrunkTailQueuePktDrops.name: jnxAtmTrunkTailQueuePktDrops
jnxAtmTrunkTailQueuePktDrops.description: The number of packets dropped due to bandwidth constraints. Indicates that packets were queued to send out at a rate faster than allowed.

jnxAtmTrunkInOAMF4AISCells.name: jnxAtmTrunkInOAMF4AISCells
jnxAtmTrunkInOAMF4AISCells.description: The number of OAM F4 cells received, with AIS(Alarm Indication Signal) bit set.

jnxAtmTrunkOutOAMF4AISCells.name: jnxAtmTrunkOutOAMF4AISCells
jnxAtmTrunkOutOAMF4AISCells.description: The number of OAM F4 cells sent, with AIS(Alarm Indication Signal) bit set.
